===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|buket}}, {{m|enm|boket}}, partly from {{der|en|ang|bucc}} {{gloss|"bucket, pitcher"; mod. dialectal {{m|en|buck}}}}, equivalent to {{suffix|en|bouk|et}}; and partly from {{der|en|xno|buket}}, {{m|fro|buquet|t=tub; pail}} (compare {{cog|nrf|boutchet}}, {{cog|nrf|bouquet}}), diminutive of {{der|en|fro|buc|t=abdomen; object with a cavity}}, from {{der|en|VL.|*būcus}} (compare {{cog|oc|-}} and {{cog|ca|buc}}, {{m+|it|buco}}, {{m|it|buca||hole, gap}}), from {{bor|en|frk|*būk|t=belly, stomach}}. Both the Old English and Frankish terms derive from {{der|en|gem-pro|*būkaz||belly, stomach}}. More at {{l|en|bouk}}.

